article.article:
4. After completion of the identity checks and physical checks, the competent authorities shall:
complete the relevant entries of Part II of the CED;
attach the results of sampling and analysis carried out, in accordance with paragraph 2 of this Article;
provide the CED with the CED reference number;
stamp and sign the original of the CED;
make and retain a copy of the signed and stamped CED.

The report shall include the following information:
number of consignments introduced, including size in terms of net weight and country of origin of each consignment;
number of consignments subjected to sampling for analysis;
results of the identity checks and physical checks referred to in Article 8(2).
